            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-356-person2950">
                  JAMES 
                  SADLER
               <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2950" type="surname" value="SADLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2950" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2950" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 26th of March I had been on an errand, and on coming back I saw the prisoner at the further end of the passage; he took my coat off the hook and put it under his apron - when he was almost out of the door I called Mr. Curry, who came and took him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I went in to ask for a person who lodged there, and a boy ran against me and dropped the coat. Witness. No, that is not true; he asked if it belonged to any one in the house, after I had called Mr. Curry.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-356-person2951">
                  JOSEPH 
                  CURRY
               <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2951" type="surname" value="CURRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2951" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2951" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was called, and took the coat from under his apron; he said he was very sorry, and would not do it again - I took him to the watch-house.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-356-person2952">
                  JOHN 
                  PEARCE
               <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2952" type="surname" value="PEARCE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2952" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2952" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I took the prisoner; I have the coat -I found a pocket-book and some duplicates upon him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A boy ran against me and dropped the coat; I said, "Does this belong to any body in the house?" - this lad said, "It belongs to me;" I said take it - this witness said to the boy, "If you say every word I tell you we shall get 7s. a day, every day we attend; you know the state your mother is in, and I am out of work" - it is for 7s. a day that the lad perjures himself; I have had the best of characters - Major 
               <persName id="t18300415-356-person2953">Dod</persName>
             left me 700l. and now I have 1200l. to receive from Government; if I get away I shall not be in England three days.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-356-person2954">
                  JOHN 
                  SADLER
               <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2954" type="surname" value="SADLER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2954" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-356-person2954" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I did not hear him say any such thing.</p>
               <p>JOHN PEARCE. Nothing of the kind happened in my presence.</p>
